From Sherlette Dixon Subject Christianity Atheism an update First I would like to thank all who sent me their opinions on the matter at All advice was taken to heart if not directly My friend found out about the matter quite After reading some of my mail I quit from the mail reader went about my I must have trashed my mail improperly because he got on the same terminal the next day saw my old He thought they were responses to a post he placed in earlier that week so he read some of them before realizing that they were for I got a message from him the next day he apologized for reading my mail said that he did not want to appear to be a He said that he would be willing to talk to me about his views didn't mind doing so especially with a So we I neither changed his mind nor did he change mine as that was not the Now he knows where I'm coming from now I know where he's coming And all that I can do is pray for him as I've always I believe the reason that he I click instead of bash heads is because I see Christianity as a tool for revolution not a tool for maintaining the status To be quite blunt I have more of a reason to reject God than he does just by the fact that I am an African American Christianity religion have been used as tools to separate my people from the true knowledge of our history the wealth of our contributions to the world The kitchen of heaven was all we had to look forward to during the slave days this mentality second class status still exists I too have rejected an aspect of Christianity that of the estabished Too much hypocricy exists behind the walls of God's house beginning with the images of a white Jesus to that of the members praise God on Sunday raise hell beginning God willing I will find a church home where I can feel comfortable at home but I don't see it happening anytime Sherlette